# Pre-Spec: Collapsible Sidebar — RiskShield

> **Status:** Pre-spec (consolidated from issues #15, #16, #17, #18)
> **Next step:** Full spec document

---

## Overview

Redesign the sidebar into a collapsible, frosted-glass component. This covers the full scope of work: refactoring the existing component, implementing the collapsible behaviour, accessibility polish, and QA sign-off.

---

## Goals

- Clean up the existing `Sidebar.tsx` (tokens, inline styles, magic strings) so it is ready for feature work.
- Add a collapsible mode: icons-only bubble with frosted glass effect when collapsed, full nav when expanded.
- Persist the user's preference across sessions.
- Ensure the component is fully accessible and respects `prefers-reduced-motion`.

---

## Scope

### 1 — Refactor (pre-condition)

> *File: `src/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx`*

- Replace all hardcoded colour literals (e.g. `"#fff"`) with design tokens (`T.sidebarText`, `T.textTer`, etc.).
- Extract repeated inline style objects into named constants or small factory functions.
- Move the keyboard shortcuts array into a named constant.

### 2 — Collapsible behaviour

> *File: `src/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx`*

- Add `isCollapsed` state; persist to `localStorage` under key `sidebarCollapsed`.
- **Collapsed:** 90 px wide, icons-only, frosted glass island (`backdrop-filter: blur(10px)`, `var(--shadow-8)`).
- **Expanded:** 260 px wide, full nav with labels, search, portfolio summary, and keyboard shortcuts.
- Smooth width + label-opacity transitions using CSS motion tokens / easing.
- Hide search, portfolio summary, and keyboard shortcuts hints when collapsed.
- Expose an expand/collapse toggle button with a descriptive `aria-label`.

### 3 — Accessibility & reduced-motion polish

> *Files: `src/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx`, `src/index.css` (if needed)*

- Collapsed nav items must expose their labels programmatically (`title` attribute, or equivalent) for tooltips and screen readers.
- All interactive elements must have appropriate `aria-*` attributes.
- Keyboard focus styles must be visible for nav items and the toggle button.
- All transitions and animations must be disabled when `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` is active.
- Keyboard-only navigation must be able to expand/collapse the sidebar and traverse all nav links.

### 4 — QA checklist

Before the feature PR is merged, confirm:

- [ ] `npm run typecheck` passes with 0 errors.
- [ ] `npm run build` succeeds.
- [ ] Cold-load: theme and branding render without flash.
- [ ] Collapsed → expanded toggle works; preference persists after reload.
- [ ] Nav items navigate to the correct pages; active state highlights correctly.
- [ ] Search is hidden when collapsed and visible when expanded.
- [ ] Keyboard shortcuts hint only appears on pointer-fine devices.
- [ ] Theme toggle still works in both states.
- [ ] No console errors or warnings in the browser.
- [ ] Screenshots (expanded and collapsed) attached to the PR.

---

## Acceptance Criteria

- Collapsed/expanded toggle works and preference persists across reloads.
- No regressions to navigation or permission gating.
- `npm run typecheck` and `npm run build` pass with 0 errors.
- Toggle has `aria-label`; collapsed nav items expose labels via `title` for screen readers.
- Transitions are suppressed under `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`.

